    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-10">
      <div class="absolute inset-0" style="background-image: url('/images/hero-booking.jpg'); background-size: cover; background-position: center;"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="container-custom relative">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <span class="inline-block bg-brand-red/20 text-brand-red-light px-3 py-1 rounded-full text-sm mb-4">Complete Guide</span>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">Tattoo Booking Software</h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 mb-4">
          <strong>Tattoo booking software</strong> lets clients book appointments online, pay deposits, and receive confirmations—all without you lifting a finger. Stop playing DM tennis and start waking up to confirmed bookings.
        </p>
        <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: January 2026 | Reading time: 8 minutes</p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4">
          <a href="https://app.mytattoo.software/signin" class="btn-primary text-lg px-8 py-4">Get started</a>
          <a href="#what-is" class="btn-secondary text-lg px-8 py-4">Read the Guide</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Featured Answer -->
  <FeaturedAnswer question="What is tattoo booking software?">
    Tattoo booking software lets clients request an appointment online and attach reference images, without DM management. MyTattoo.Software turns your Instagram bio link into a branded booking page: clients leave their details, you send back a quote and time slot, and the appointment is confirmed only once they pay the deposit — so it never lands on your calendar unpaid.
  </FeaturedAnswer>

  <!-- Statistics Section -->
  <StatisticsSection
    site="tattoo"
    pageUrl="https://mytattoo.software/tattoo-booking-software/"
    title="Tattoo Booking Industry Overview"
    stats={bookingStats}
  />

  <!-- Table of Contents -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-4">In This Guide</h2>
          <ul class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-2 text-gray-700">
            <li><a href="#what-is" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ What Is Booking Software?</a></li>
            <li><a href="#why-need" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ Why You Need It</a></li>
            <li><a href="#how-works" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ How Online Booking Works</a></li>
            <li><a href="#deposits" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ Deposit Collection</a></li>
            <li><a href="#no-shows" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ Reducing No-Shows</a></li>
            <li><a href="#features" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ Key Features</a></li>
            <li><a href="#choosing" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ Choosing the Right Software</a></li>
            <li><a href="#faq" class="hover:text-brand-red">→ FAQ</a></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto prose prose-lg">

        <h2 id="what-is" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-6">What Is Tattoo Booking Software?</h2>

        <p><strong>Tattoo booking software</strong> is an online system that lets clients schedule appointments, pay deposits, and receive confirmations automatically. Instead of endless DM chains and phone tag, clients see your real availability and book when it works for them.</p>

        <p>The best tattoo booking software is built specifically for the industry—handling consultations, multi-hour sessions, deposit collection, and appointment types that generic tools like Calendly can't manage properly.</p>

        <h2 id="why-need" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Why You Need Online Booking</h2>

        <p>You became a tattoo artist to create art, not spend hours managing a calendar. Without proper booking software, you're leaving money on the table and burning out on admin.</p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">The Problem With DM Booking</h3>

        <div class="bg-bone-hi border-l-4 border-brand-red p-4 my-6">
          <p class="font-bold text-brand-navy">Every ignored DM is lost revenue</p>
          <p>While you're tattooing, potential clients are messaging you. By the time you reply, they've often booked with someone else. Online booking captures these clients while you work.</p>
        </div>

        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Time sink:</strong> 5-10 messages to book one appointment. That's hours per week on scheduling alone.</li>
          <li><strong>Lost bookings:</strong> Clients want to book at 11pm when they're browsing Instagram. DMs don't convert at midnight.</li>
          <li><strong>No deposits = no-shows:</strong> Without payment at booking, 20-30% of appointments never happen.</li>
          <li><strong>Double bookings:</strong> Keeping track manually means mistakes. Software eliminates conflicts.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Benefits of Booking Software</h3>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li><strong>24/7 booking</strong> — wake up to booking requests, ready to quote</li>
          <li><strong>Fewer no-shows</strong> — a paid deposit means clients have skin in the game</li>
          <li><strong>Zero scheduling conflicts</strong> — real-time availability updates</li>
          <li><strong>More time for art</strong> — stop being a full-time administrator</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="how-works" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">How Online Booking Works</h2>

        <p>Modern tattoo booking software creates a seamless experience for both you and your clients.</p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">The Client Experience</h3>

        <ol class="space-y-2">
          <li><strong>1. Client clicks your booking link</strong> — from Instagram bio, website, or Google listing</li>
          <li><strong>2. Selects appointment type</strong> — consultation, small piece, half-day session, touch-up</li>
          <li><strong>3. Picks available time</strong> — sees your real-time availability, no guessing</li>
          <li><strong>4. Enters their info</strong> — contact details, tattoo description, reference images</li>
          <li><strong>5. Pays deposit</strong> — secure card payment processed instantly</li>
          <li><strong>6. Receives confirmation</strong> — an email with all appointment details</li>
        </ol>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">What You See</h3>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>New booking notification by email</li>
          <li>Deposit automatically in your account</li>
          <li>Client info and reference images stored</li>
          <li>Calendar updated with no conflicts</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="deposits" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Deposit Collection</h2>

        <p>Deposit collection is the single most important feature of booking software. Without it, you're gambling on every appointment.</p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Why Deposits Matter</h3>

        <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg my-6">
          <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">$500 session × 20% no-show rate = $100 lost per booking</p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">If you do 20 sessions a month without deposits, that's $2,000+ in lost income. A $50-100 deposit fixes this problem almost entirely.</p>
        </div>

        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li><strong>Financial commitment:</strong> Clients who pay upfront show up. Period.</li>
          <li><strong>Professional image:</strong> Deposits signal that your time is valuable.</li>
          <li><strong>Cancellation protection:</strong> Keep the deposit if they no-show without notice.</li>
          <li><strong>Cash flow:</strong> Deposits provide predictable income before sessions.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Deposit Best Practices</h3>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Amount:</strong> $50-100 or 20-30% of estimated total</li>
          <li><strong>Policy:</strong> Non-refundable, applies to session cost</li>
          <li><strong>Timing:</strong> Required at booking, not later</li>
          <li><strong>Clear terms:</strong> State your cancellation policy upfront</li>
        </ul>

        <!-- Calculator Callout -->
        <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #F4E4E1 0%, #F3ECDD 100%); border-left: 4px solid #A62B22; padding: 1.5rem; border-radius: 0.5rem; margin: 2rem 0;">
          <div style="display: flex; align-items: start; gap: 1rem;">
            <div style="flex-shrink: 0; width: 48px; height: 48px; background: #A62B22; border-radius: 0.5rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
              <svg style="width: 28px; height: 28px; color: white;" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 7h6m0 10v-3m-3 3h.01M9 17h.01M9 14h.01M12 14h.01M15 11h.01M12 11h.01M9 11h.01M7 21h10a2 2 0 002-2V5a2 2 0 00-2-2H7a2 2 0 00-2 2v14a2 2 0 002 2z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 1;">
              <h3 style="font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: #17120E; margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;">See How Deposits Impact Your Revenue</h3>
              <p style="color: #241B14; margin: 0 0 1rem 0; line-height: 1.6;">Calculate exactly how much revenue you're losing to no-shows and what implementing deposits could recover. Our free calculator models your booking utilisation and shows the real financial impact of deposit policies.</p>
              <a href="/tattoo-studio-calculator/" style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; color: #A62B22; font-weight: 600; text-decoration: none;">
                Calculate Your No-Show Impact →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="no-shows" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Reducing No-Shows</h2>

        <p>Booking software attacks no-shows from multiple angles—not just deposits.</p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Email Notifications</h3>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li><strong>New request:</strong> You're notified the moment a client submits a booking request</li>
          <li><strong>Offer sent:</strong> The client gets an email with your quote, time slot, and deposit link</li>
          <li><strong>Deposit paid:</strong> You and the client both get confirmation once the deposit clears</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Combined with a deposit requirement, clear communication at every step is what keeps no-shows down — clients know exactly where they stand, and nothing sits unconfirmed in a DM thread.</p>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Easy Rescheduling</h3>

        <p>Give clients a simple way to reschedule if something comes up. It's better than a no-show. Good software includes self-service rescheduling with reasonable notice requirements.</p>

        <h2 id="features" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Key Features to Look For</h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Deposit Collection</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Collect payments at booking time. If software doesn't do this, keep looking.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Email Notifications</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Automatic emails on every step — new request, offer sent, deposit paid — for you and the client.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Custom Booking Types</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Consultations, small pieces, large sessions—each needs different time blocks and deposits.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Reference Image Upload</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Let clients share inspiration images at booking time, not through separate DMs.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Deposit-Gated Calendar</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">The appointment only appears on your calendar once the deposit has cleared.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-6 rounded-lg">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Mobile Friendly</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">Clients book on phones. Your booking page must work perfectly on mobile.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <p>Related: <a href="/tattoo-studio-software/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">Tattoo Studio Software: Complete Guide</a></p>

        <h2 id="choosing" class="text-3xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-12 mb-6">Choosing the Right Software</h2>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">Built for Tattoo vs. Generic</h3>

        <p>Generic booking tools (Calendly, Acuity, Square Appointments) work for basic scheduling but lack tattoo-specific features:</p>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li>Reference image collection at booking</li>
          <li>No client account required to book</li>
          <li>Proper handling of multi-hour sessions</li>
          <li>Deposit policies that match industry norms</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-navy mt-8 mb-4">What to Avoid</h3>

        <ul class="space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Per-booking fees:</strong> Punishes success. Flat monthly is better.</li>
          <li><strong>No deposit collection:</strong> The most important feature. Non-negotiable.</li>
          <li><strong>No confirmation emails:</strong> Clients and artists should both know where a booking stands.</li>
          <li><strong>Complicated setup:</strong> If it takes more than an hour to configure, it's too complex.</li>
        </ul>

        <p>Related: <a href="/blog/free-tattoo-booking-app-guide/" class="text-brand-red hover:underline">Free Tattoo Booking Apps: What Actually Works</a></p>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Comparison Table -->
  <ComparisonTable
    title="MyTattoo vs Generic Booking Tools vs Manual DM Booking"
    headers={['MyTattoo', 'Generic Tools', 'Manual/DMs']}
    rows={comparisonData}
  />

  <!-- FAQ Section -->
  <section id="faq">
    <FAQEnhanced
      site="tattoo"
      pageUrl="https://mytattoo.software/tattoo-booking-software/"
      title="Frequently Asked Questions About Tattoo Booking Software"
      faqs={faqItems}
    />
  </section>

  <!-- Remaining Content -->
  <section class="section bg-white">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="section bg-gradient-to-r from-brand-red to-blood-deep text-white">
    <div class="container-custom text-center">
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Ready to Stop Chasing Bookings?</h2>
      <p class="text-xl mb-8 opacity-90">MyTattoo.Software lets clients book 24/7 and pay a deposit before it's confirmed. Wake up to booking requests instead of full DM inboxes.</p>
      <a href="https://app.mytattoo.software/signin" class="btn bg-white text-brand-red hover:bg-gray-100 text-lg px-8 py-4">Get started</a>
      <p class="text-sm mt-4 opacity-75">MyTattoo is deposit-secured booking for independent tattoo artists.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Content -->
  <section class="section bg-gray-50">
    <div class="container-custom">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-brand-navy mb-8 text-center">Related Guides</h2>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <a href="/tattoo-studio-software/" class="card p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Studio Software Guide</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Complete platform for tattoo shops and studios</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/tattoo-artist-software/" class="card p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Artist Software Guide</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">Tools for independent tattoo artists</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/blog/free-tattoo-booking-app-guide/" class="card p-6 hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow">
          <h3 class="font-bold text-brand-navy mb-2">Free Booking Apps</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">What free tools can and can't do</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
